<xar:template xmlns:xar="http://xaraya.com/2004/blocklayout">
    <h4>Which template do I edit?</h4>
    <p>When working on a theme you should edit 
    <em>override</em>theme templates not internal system templates. Turn on 
    <em>Show template filenames in HTML comments</em>in the Themes Modify Config page. This allows
    you to see which template is providing output by simply looking at the page source. Once you
    have identified a template, create an 
    <strong>override</strong>template in your theme. Learn how you can 
    <a href="http://xaraya.com/index.php/documentation/25">override templates</a>with an Articles
    module example.</p>
</xar:template>